The basic education department is concerned as some schools had to close their gates again. JOHANNESBURG - The basic education department is concerned as some schools had to close their gates again. There have been reports of COVID-19 cases forcing them to temporarily shut down. READ: High school principal accused of corruption This comes as the country moved to adjusted lockdown level one. The department and its stakeholders are urging people to continue being vigilant amid the ongoing pandemic. eNCA’s Tshegohaco Moagi shares more details in the video above.